rec1HpJUVhCegp5Vk","target":"recr71Fz4NHTnGLJ2","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recH1FutzCilVHrzJ","ref":"Exod.15.1","text":"Then sang Moses and the children of Israel this song unto the LORD, and spake, saying, I will sing unto the LORD, for he hath triumphed gloriously: the horse and his rider hath he thrown into the sea.","year":-1491},{"id":"recAfvhIIz8G2XlVr","ref":"Exod.15.2","text":"The LORD is my strength and song, and he is become my salvation: he is my God, and I will prepare him an habitation; my father’s God, and I will exalt him.","year":-1491},{"id":"recR16dJ1fjT2effI","ref":"Exod.15.3","text":"The LORD is a man of war: the LORD is his name.","year":-1491},{"id":"recPsbP6iei3oGQO9","ref":"Exod.15.4","text":"Pharaoh’s chariots and his host hath he cast into the sea: his chosen captains also are drowned in the Red sea.","year":-1491},{"id":"recpu2zMAK64Gnqnw","ref":"Exod.15.5","text":"The depths have covered them: they sank into the bottom as a stone.","year":-1491},{"id":"recK77bQHhI8hKzkM","ref":"Exod.15.6","text":"Thy right hand, O LORD, is become glorious in power: thy right hand, O LORD, hath dashed in pieces the enemy.","year":-1491},{"id":"recQjlvU3c0HtMGHe","ref":"Exod.15.7","text":"And in the greatness of thine excellency thou hast overthrown them that rose up against thee: thou sentest forth thy wrath, which consumed them as stubble.","year":-1491},{"id":"reck7rZc7nZJUhjVc","ref":"Exod.15.8","text":"And with the blast of thy nostrils the waters were gathered together, the floods stood upright as an heap, and the depths were congealed in the heart of the sea.","year":-1491}]}
